SIMPLE: stab
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stab
<hw>Stab</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Stabbed</conjf> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧bd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Stabbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. OD.
<ets>staven</ets> to fix, fasten, fr. <ets>stave</ets>,
<ets>staff</ets>, a staff, rod; akin to G. <ets>stab</ets> a staff,
stick, E. <ets>staff</ets>; also Gael. <ets>stob</ets> to stab, as n., a
stake, a stub. Cf. <er>Staff</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pierce
with a pointed weapon; to wound or kill by the thrust of a pointed
instrument; <as>as, to <ex>stab</ex> a man with a dagger</as>; also, to
thrust; <as>as, to <ex>stab</ex> a dagger into a person</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To injure secretly or by malicious falsehood
or slander; <as>as, to <ex>stab</ex> a person's
reputation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stab
<hw>Stab</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give a wound with a
pointed weapon; to pierce; to thrust with a pointed weapon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>None shall dare⟦br⟧
With shortened sword to <qex>stab</qex> in closer war.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To wound or pain, as if with a pointed
weapon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She speaks poniards, and every word <qex>stabs</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To stab at</b></col>, <cd>to offer or threaten to stab;
to thrust a pointed weapon at.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stab
<hw>Stab</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The thrust of a pointed
weapon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wound with a sharp-pointed weapon; <as>as, to fall
by the <ex>stab</ex> of an assassin</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: An injury inflicted covertly or suddenly;
<as>as, a <ex>stab</ex> given to character</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stabat Mater</ent>⟦br⟧
